5000|$|Marius Kohl (born 16 September 1953) is {{the former}} chief of the Luxembourg tax agency Sociétés 6. During his 22-year tenure, he was solely {{responsible}} for approving thousands of <b>tax</b> <b>arrangements</b> for foreign companies investing capital in Luxembourg. He retired in 2013. Kohl was known by the nickname [...] "Monsieur Ruling" [...] andhas been credited with helping to secure €1.2 billion in annual tax revenue for Luxembourg.|$|E
